{"title_page": "Nouman Ali Khan", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Nouman Ali Khan\n| image              =\n| caption            = Nouman Ali Khan in 2015\n| birth_date         = \n| birth_place        = [[Germany]]\n| nationality        = American\n| occupation         = Speaker\n| known_for          = Arabic and Quranic Studies\n| title              = Bayyinah Institute, founder\n| awards             = 500 Most Influential Muslim\n| website            = {{URL|http://bayyinah.tv}}\n| footnotes          = \n{{Infobox YouTube personality\n| channel_direct_url = user/BayyinahInstitute\n| channel_display_name = Bayyinah Institute\n| subscribers        = 861K\n| subscriber_date    = \n| views              = 90,505,151\n| view_date          = \n| years_active       = Feb 20, 2009\n| gold_button        = \n| gold_year          = \n| stats_update       = \n}}\n\n\n\n}}\n\n'''Nouman Ali Khan''' is a [[Pakistani-American]]<ref>Hussein Kesvani, ''Follow Me, Akhi: The Online World of British Muslims'', Oxford University Press, 2019, p. 17</ref> [[Da'i|Muslim speaker]] and Arabic instructor who founded the Bayyinah Institute for Arabic and Qur\u2019anic Studies after serving as an instructor of [[Arabic]] at [[Nassau Community College]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://theMuslim500.com/profile/khan-nouman-ali | title=The Muslim 500: Nouman Ali Khan | accessdate=2015-06-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.nbcbayarea.com/news/national-international/Imams-US-Mosques-Islam-224710772.html | title=Demand for U.S.-Born Imams Up in American Mosques | first=Gillian | last=Flaccus | date=2013-09-21 | accessdate=2015-06-17}}</ref> He has been named one of the 500 most influential Muslims in the world by the Royal Islamic Strategic Studies Centre of Jordan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://themuslim500.com/profile/khan-nouman-ali | title=The Muslim 500: Nouman Ali Khan}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nKhan was born in Germany to a [[Pashtuns|pashtun]] Pakistani family and spent his preschool years in the former East Berlin.<ref>http://www.timeskuwait.com/Times_Nouman-Ali-Khan---The-Man--The-Mission-and-The-Media \"Nouman Ali Khan - The Man, The Mission and The Media\", ''The Times Kuwait'', 17 February 2015.</ref> His father then worked for the Pakistan Embassy in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, where Khan attended the Pakistan Embassy school from grades 2 to 8. His father moved the family to New York when Khan was in his teens.<ref>http://www.arabnews.com/news/445647 Sameen Tahir Khan, \"Nouman Khan: The one-man Qur\u2019an movement\", ''Arab News'', 22 March 2013.</ref>\n\n==Online teaching ==\nWhen Ustadh Nouman Ali Khan started bayyinah [https://bayyinahtv.com/] TV, his goal was to redefine the way Quran and [[Arabic]] were taught. Listed among the 500 most influential Muslims in the world, he has inspired millions of online subscribers across the globe with his simple, clear and entertaining approach to unraveling complex subjects in the Quran.\n\n<br />\n\n== Publications ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\nPublications By Nouman Ali Khan\n!Title\n!Description\n!Date\n!Language\n|-\n|''Divine Speech: Exploring Quran As Literature''\n|Bayyinah Publishing in 2016\n|2016\n|English\n|-\n|''Revive Your Heart: Putting Life in Perspective''\n|Kube Publishing {{ISBN|978-0986275043}}\n|2017\n|English\n|-\n|''Bondhon''\n|Guardian Publication; 1st edition '''ASIN:''' B07KV37PVR\n|2010\n|Bangla\n|-\n|''Arabic With Husna''\n|Multiple Volumes {{ISBN|978-0986275043}}\n|\n|English\n|-\n|''Dirilt Kalbini''\n|Tima\u015f Yay\u0131nlar\u0131 (2017) {{ISBN|978-6050825992}}\n|\n|[[Turkish language|Turkish]]\n|-\n|''Revive Your Heart''\n|Guardian Publication\n|2019\n|[[Bangla language|Bangla]]\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official website|bayyinah.com}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Khan, Nouman Ali}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American Muslims]]\n[[Category:People from Dallas]]\n[[Category:American expatriates in 